text: Atal () is a rural locality (a selo) in Yaksatovsky Selsoviet, Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 643 as of 2010. There are 36 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Kizan River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast
title: Atal, Astrakhan Oblast
